03/12/2007
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- Kosovo Democratic Party (PDK) leader Hashim Thaci said on Saturday (December 1st) that he plans to meet with the leaders of all political parties in Kosovo and invite them to join the new ruling coalition. Thaci, whose party won the November 17th parliamentary elections in the province, told reporters that after the final election results are announced, he will try to integrate all parliamentary parties in the new government, saying only a broad government would respect the choice of voters. Preliminary results suggest the PDK won 34% of the vote, followed by the Democratic League of Kosovo with 22%. The other parties that met the threshold of support are the Alliance for a New Kosovo, the Democratic League of Dardania and the Alliance for the Future of Kosovo. (Kosovalive, RTK - 02/12/07)
